Make select pull down menu pop a bit. Found these articles:
https://speckyboy.com/open-source-css-javascript-select-box-snippets/
https://codepen.io/wallaceerick/pen/ctsCz

NOTE, this code uses compass and sass.
Scotts-MacBook-Pro:select_plus_plus scottlarribeau$ which compass
/Users/scottlarribeau/.rvm/gems/ruby-2.3.4/bin/compass


to build button.css, enter the following command
Scotts-MacBook-Pro:select_plus_plus scottlarribeau$ compass compile
    write stylesheets/buttons.css

Note that compass expects two subdirectories:
1) sass
2) stylesheets

Scotts-MacBook-Pro:select_plus_plus scottlarribeau$ tree
.
├── README
├── config.rb
├── foo.html
├── sass
│   ├── buttons.scss
│   ├── ie.scss
│   ├── print.scss
│   └── screen.scss
├── script.js
├── style.css
└── stylesheets
    ├── buttons.css
    ├── ie.css
    ├── ie.css.bak
    ├── print.css
    └── screen.css

2 directories, 14 files

